We recommended that the Municipal Mayor, through the Municipal Budget Officer, Municipal Treasurer and MPDC:
i. Prepare the quarterly Report on Fund Utilization and Status of Program/Project Implementation;
ii. Post the said report in at least three (3) conspicuous public places in the locality and on the LGUs website within twenty (20) calendar days from the end of each quarter;
iii. Send written notice on compliance thereof to the DBM, DILG, NTF-ELCAC, House of Representatives, Senate of the Philippines, and the House Committee on Appropriations; and
iv. Furnish the Audit Team with the quarterly report, proof of posting and written notification to the respective Offices duly supported with appropriate documentation for monitoring purposes.

We recommended and the Municipal Accountant agreed to:
Prepare separate subsidiary ledgers for each road component and LRN Ledger Cards for each local road;
Present in the Notes to Financial Statements the required disclosures pertaining to the road network system;
We also recommended and the General Services Officer agreed to:
Prepare and maintain a Report on the Physical Count of the Road Network System and the Road Map in coordination with the other members of the Inventory Committee;
Keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components; and
We further recommended and the Municipal Engineer agreed to:
Provide assistance to the Municipal Accountant and Treasurer in determining the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects.

We reiterated the following recommendations:
a.	 For the variance due to the CY 2009 balances taken up in bulk category in the computerized accounting system, the Municipal Accountant/ GSO shall examine available PPE records in CY 2008 to help in the identification of items for physical count and reconciliation;

b. For the variance coming from PPE records entered on CY 2009 onwards, Management shall identify items which are missing during physical count using the detailed PPE list to be generated from the accounting system; and act whether to hold the assigned personnel accountable or apply for request for relief from accountability after due investigation of the cause of loss of property.

